f=Engineering/ops/marketplace/deployment-patterns/SKILL.md · h1:Deployment Patterns=Production deployment workflows CI/CD best practices. **VYON preconditions (senior):** nothing runs until release-discipline's gates green quinn GATE PASS, charter verdict, rollback exercised FIRST. Database steps inside any deploy dana-authored scripts OPERATOR runs (Rail 3). · h2:When to Activate=Setting CI/CD pipelines dockerizing application choosing deployment strategy implementing health checks/readiness probes preparing production release environment configuration. · h3:Rolling (default)=Replace instances gradually; old new run simultaneously during rollout. **Pros:** zero downtime, gradual. **Cons:** two versions live once changes backward-compatible (pairs dana's expand-contract). **Use:** standard, backward-compatible deploys. · h3:Blue-Green=Two identical environments; traffic switches atomically; old side becomes standby. **Pros:** instant rollback (switch back), clean cutover. **Cons:** infrastructure during deploy. **Use:** critical services, zero tolerance. · h3:Canary=Small traffic percentage new version first (5% 50% 100% metrics hold). **Pros:** real-traffic validation before full rollout. **Cons:** needs traffic splitting monitoring. **Use:** high-traffic services, risky changes, feature flags. · h2:Docker (dated examples bind business platform-playbooks)=**Multi-stage pattern (any language):** deps stage build stage minimal runtime stage; non-root user; production artifacts copied; `HEALTHCHECK` instruction; pinned base-image versions. Source carries full Node 1.22 Python 3.12 Dockerfiles copy upstream business adopts one. **Good practices:** specific version tags (never `:latest`) multi-stage minimize size non-root user dependency files copied first (layer caching) `.dockerignore` (node_modules, .git, tests) HEALTHCHECK resource limits. **Bad:** root user `:latest` whole-repo single COPY dev deps prod image **secrets image** (env vars secrets manager only). · h2:CI/CD Pipeline=`PR:            lint → typecheck → unit → integration → preview deploy \· Merge to main: lint → typecheck → unit → integration → build image \· → deploy staging → smoke tests → deploy production` · h2:CI/CD Pipeline=**Stages:** GitHub Actions reference pipeline source (test job build+push image tagged SHA environment-gated deploy job); Harness.io proposed connector ops's tooling map either way pipeline enforces: deploy job without test job green, production behind environment gate, images traceable commit SHA. · h2:Health Checks=**Liveness** (`/health`): cheap 200/ok process alive., **Detailed/readiness** (`/health/detailed`): checks dependency (DB, cache, external APIs), returns 503 per-check status degraded, includes version uptime. Endpoint implementation raj's `backend-observability`; ops consumes probes monitors., **K8s probes (dated example):** livenessProbe (30s period, failures) readinessProbe (10s, failures) startupProbe (5s 150s max startup). · h2:Environment Configuration=**Twelve-factor:** config environment variables, never code; secrets injected secrets manager; explicit `APP_ENV`. **Validate config startup fail fast** (schema-validate env: required URLs, minimum secret lengths, enumerated environments) misconfigured deploy die boot, first request. · h2:Rollback Strategy=Instant rollback mechanics (dated examples): `kubectl rollout undo` `vercel rollback` redeploy previous SHA. **DB rollback never platform command** reversible migrations dana-authored, operator-run (Rail 3). **Rollback checklist (feeds release-discipline's rollback-exercised-FIRST rule):** · h2:Rollback Strategy=Previous image/artifact available tagged, migrations backward-compatible (no destructive changes in-flight), Feature flags disable new features without deploy, Alerts configured error-rate spikes, Rollback tested staging before production release · h2:Production Readiness Checklist=**Application:** test tiers pass hardcoded secrets error handling covers edges structured JSON logs, PII meaningful health endpoint. **Infrastructure:** reproducible pinned image builds env vars documented validated startup resource limits scaling bounds TLS everywhere. **Monitoring:** request rate/latency/error metrics exported error-rate alerts log aggregation uptime checks health endpoint. **Security:** dependency CVE scan (aegis's pipeline) CORS allowlist rate limiting public endpoints authn/authz verified security headers (CSP, HSTS, X-Frame-Options). **Operations:** rollback plan documented tested migrations tested production scale runbooks common failures escalation path defined. · b:with other skills=**release-discipline (ops, custom):** AUTHORITY gate preconditions, rollback-first, deploy checklist, expand-migrate-contract sequencing. skill supplies strategy/mechanics; conflicts resolve release-discipline., **platform-playbooks (ops):** platform-specific snippet (Docker, Actions, K8s, Vercel) lives operationally dated per-business playbook; file pattern source., **maintenance-hygiene (ops):** monitoring baselines, dependency/CVE cadence, backup restore-testing., **incident-response (ops):** deploy breaks roll back first, diagnose second; post-mortem feeds regression-map., **migration-discipline database-migrations (dana):** phases inside deploys dana authors, operator runs, ops sequences., **backend-observability (raj):** owns health/metrics endpoints skill probes., **test-strategy (quinn):** GATE PASS precondition; smoke tests pipeline quinn-defined tiers., **Security Charter:** senior everything here.